{"lemma":"نُمْرٌ","slug":"نُمْرٌ","root":"ن.م.ر","root_slug":"ن-م-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-م-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40554","n40555","n40557","n40558"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%85%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"splotched, spotted"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ن م ر (n m r)."},"ipa":["/ʔan.mar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40554","headword_ar":"نَمِرَ","root":"nmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor. -, (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namarN","text_ar":"نَمَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2853},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, spotted like a leopard"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panther:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see also 5:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a cloud, or collection of clouds,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became of the colour of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namir","text_ar":"نَمِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leopard"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panther"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spots being seen in their interstices."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)       -A2-  See also 5, in three places."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n40555","headword_ar":"نمّر","root":"nmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanomiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered, and rendered morose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"his face. (T.)       -A2-  See also 5, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40557","headword_ar":"نِمْرٌ","root":"nmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namirN","text_ar":"نَمِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n40558","headword_ar":"نَمِرٌ","root":"nmr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomaru","text_ar":"اَنْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namirN","text_ar":"نَمِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimorN","text_ar":"نِمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb, K,) which is a contraction of the former, (Msb,) or a dial. form, (TA,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leopard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain wild beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K, &c.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more malignant than the lion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and bolder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so called because of his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numar","text_ar":"نُمَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spots"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being of divers colours,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called in Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Palanoko","text_ar":"پَلَنْكْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomurN","text_ar":"اَنْمُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomaArN","text_ar":"اَنْمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numuwrN","text_ar":"نُمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) held by Th to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimorN","text_ar":"نِمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numuwrapN","text_ar":"نُمُورَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, and so in some copies of the K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numurN","text_ar":"نُمُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) which occurs in poetry, and is anomalous, perhaps a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numuwrN","text_ar":"نُمُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and not mentioned by Sb, (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numorN","text_ar":"نُمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which is the most common in occurrence, but, accord. to Th, he who uses it makes the sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anomaru","text_ar":"اَنْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimaArN","text_ar":"نِمَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) held by Th to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimorN","text_ar":"نِمْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nimaArapN","text_ar":"نِمَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) As the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namir","text_ar":"نَمِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is one of the most abominable and malignant of wild beasts, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labisa fulaAnN lifulaAnK jiloda Aln~amiri","text_ar":"لَبِسَ فُلَانٌ لِفُلَانٍ جِلْدَ النَّمِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one became changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered, to such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"met him in a morose manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became very rancourous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malicious, towards him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) The kings of the Arabs, when they sat [in judgment] to slay a man, used to attire themselves in skins of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namir","text_ar":"نَمِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then give orders for the slaying of him whom they desired to slay. (IB.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"namiyrN","text_ar":"نَمِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", throughout."}],"source_refs":["M","A","Msb","K","TA","T","Mgh","S","IB"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}